<PageLayout meta={{ title: "Home" }}>
	<section>
		<h1 class="title mb-12">Hey!</h1>
		<p class="mb-4">
			I am Kasturi Kandalam, a Pre-Doc at Indian Statistical Institute - Delhi (ISI-D). The breadth of my research covers how social institutions and access to public services shape individual agency and life outcomes. I build and work with large-scale administrative and spatial datasets to uncover patterns that are often invisible at the aggregate level. I enjoy the technical challenges of data work as much as the conceptual puzzles embedded in real-world behaviour.
		

			I hold a Master’s in Economics and a Bachelor’s in Economics (Honours) from Azim Premji University, Bengaluru. Previously, I worked with <a href="https://www.core-econ.org/">CORE Economics Education</a>, <a href="https://azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in/centre-for-the-study-of-the-indian-economy-csie/cse">Centre for Sustainable Employment</a>, and <a href="https://thedocs.worldbank.org/en/doc/771211575476485169-0090022019/render/DEJURENov2019.pdf"></a> DE JURE, DIME at The World Bank, where I contributed to projects on labour markets, social protection, and pedagogy in economics. 
		
		If you'd like to talk about data, econ, or constructing counterfactuals, you can reach me at: <a href="mailto:kasturiveemohan@gmail.com">kasturiveemohan@gmail.com</a>
		</p>
		<p class="mb-4">
			p.s. I have a soft spot for messy data.
		</p>
		<SocialList />
	</section>

	<section class="mt-16">
		<h2 class="title mb-6 text-2xl">Recent Work</h2>
